    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This mask targets dry, brittle, or colour-treated hair. ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "Avocado oil (cosmetic)",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmps3th1q0000qcv41izqcxy9"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " is one of the few carrier oils that penetrates the hair shaft rather than just coating it, making it especially effective for treating dryness from within. Honey retains moisture at the surface while rosemary essential oil supports scalp circulation.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Ingredients",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "Avocado oil (cosmetic)",
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "amount": 3,
              "prepNote": "about 45 ml; reduce to 2 tbsp for fine hair",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmps1q4eh0002xov4ycygsq8i",
              "ingredientSlug": "avocado-oil"
            },
            {
              "name": "Honey",
              "unit": "tbsp",
              "amount": 1,
              "prepNote": "about 20 g; runny honey is easiest to mix",
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientId": "cmp49fazr00e4rkv4zukxsq02",
              "ingredientSlug": "honey"
            },
            {
              "name": "Rosemary essential oil",
              "unit": "drops",
              "amount": 5,
              "prepNote": "about 0.25 ml; omit during first trimester of pregnancy",
              "isOptional": true,
              "ingredientId": "cmpeur4ce0000lgv4uu9izwfc",
              "ingredientSlug": "essential-oil-rosemary"
            }
          ],
          "defaultServings": 1
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If the honey is stiff, warm it for 10 seconds in the microwave to make it pourable. Mix the avocado oil, honey, and rosemary essential oil in a small bowl and stir until combined.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Apply",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Apply to dry or damp hair from mid-length to the ends, avoiding the scalp unless your hair is very dry at the root. Work through to the tips. Gather the hair on top of the head and wrap in a warm, damp towel or a shower cap. Leave for 20 to 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rinse out",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rinse out with warm water, then shampoo thoroughly -- oil masks need two rounds of shampoo to fully clear. Condition as normal. The hair will feel softer and look glossier from the first use.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hair type notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best for dry, thick, curly, or colour-treated hair. For fine or oily hair, reduce the oil to 1 tablespoon and apply only to the ends. Use once a week for damaged hair, once a month for maintenance.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
